abstract: While Wall Street may have cheered the regaining of the House of Representatives by Republicans, some individual financiers fared less well in their races.
snippet: While Wall Street may have cheered the regaining of the House of Representatives by Republicans, some individual financiers fared less well in their races.
lead_paragraph: 12:33 p.m. | Updated While Wall Street may have cheered the regaining of the House of Representatives by Republicans in Tuesday’s midterm elections, some individual financiers fared less well in their races.

headline.main: Some Financiers Fare Poorly in Electoral Races
